SITE ANALYSIS - MANUAL RUN
==========================

Full site analysis:
  sudo bash ~/site-analysis-tools/site-analysis.sh <site-name>

WiFi dead spot survey (walk around and mark locations):
  bash ~/site-analysis-tools/wifi-survey.sh <site-name>

  Controls:
    m = Mark location
    n = Quick note
    s = Stats snapshot
    q = Quit — full summary + channel analysis + recommendations

  Marking a location:
    1. Auto-captures signal stability, noise, SSIDs, retries
    2. Prompts — most are single keypress (no Enter needed):
       - Location name     (type + Enter)
       - Floor level       (press 1-7 instantly)
       - Room type         (press 1-9 instantly)
       - Indoor/outdoor    (press 1 or 2 instantly)
       - Distance          (type metres + Enter)
       - Walls             (press 1-6 instantly)
       - Wall material     (press 1-6 instantly)
       - Glass doors       (press 1-4 instantly)
       - Interference      (toggle 1-7 on/off, Enter when done)
       - Notes             (type + Enter, or just Enter to skip)
    3. Shows summary — press c to save, 1-9/0 to edit a field, x to cancel
    4. Auto-runs gateway ping, internet ping, DNS, HTTP TTFB tests

    Press 0 at any menu for custom input. Press b to go back.

  Background (automatic):
    - Signal/noise/bitrate/retries logged every 2s
    - Gateway ping logged every 1s
    - AP roaming detection

  Output files (in ~/site-analysis-tools/surveys/):
    *_survey_*.csv      per-location data + test results
    *_ssids_*.csv       all SSIDs at each location
    *_timeseries_*.csv  continuous signal samples (2s)
    *_ping_*.csv        continuous gateway pings (1s)
    *_survey_*.log      human-readable log

Reports saved to: ~/site-analysis-tools/reports/
Surveys saved to: ~/site-analysis-tools/surveys/
Both prompt to send to dev server when done.

Also available:
  wavemon                - real-time signal TUI
  linssid                - graphical WiFi scanner with channel graphs
  sudo horst -i wlan0   - raw WiFi monitor
